Media entrepreneur, Record Label Executive and seasoned Broadcaster, Kenny ‘Keke’ Ogungbe has called on Nigerians to pray for popular Nigerian musician, Eedris Abdulkareem who is currently undergoing dialysis in a Lagos Hospital.
Baba Keke, as he is fondly called, took to his official Instagram account, @kennyogungbe, few hour ago, to share video of Eedris Abdulkareem undergoing dialysis in a Lagos Hospital, and in the caption for the video, he called on Nigerians to pray for the ‘Nigeria Jaga Jaga’ crooner.
Famous Nigerian rapper, musician, and right activist, Eedris Abdulkareem has been diagnosed with kidney failure recently and has been undergoing dialysis since it’s detection in a Lagos Hospital.
Eedris Abdulkareem is now due for a kidney transplant at the end of July, and all arrangements and tests have been concluded according to reports from various news platforms.
Meanwhile, reactions have been pouring-in from some Nigerian celebrities and some followers of Kenny Ogungbe on Instagram as they all took to the comment section to pray for Eedris Abdulkareem. See their reactions beneath.




